PN,31805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777709146
OL,3,CSuperdry co-founder James Holder found
OL,4,Cguilty of rape
OL,6,FHolder replied: "That's not correct.
OL,7,FShe fell straight to sleep. She was
OL,8,Ffast asleep, so I popped my clothes on
OL,9,Fand left."
OL,11,FMr Haskell was asked: "Is the truth
OL,12,Fthat it suddenly dawned on you of the
OL,13,Freality of what you had just done, and
OL,14,Fyou wanted to get out of the flat as
OL,15,Fsoon as possible?"
OL,17,FHolder replied: "No, not true."
OL,19,FThe defendant, of Cheltenham,
OL,20,FGloucestershire, was remanded into
OL,21,Fcustody ahead of sentencing.
